==English==

===Etymology===
French ''[[facétieux]]'', from Latin ''[[facetia]]'' 'jest'.

===Adjective===
'''facetious'''
# Treating serious issues with deliberately inappropriate humor; [[flippant]]
# Pleasantly [[humourous]], [[jocular]]
====Translations====
*Finnish: [[vitsikäs]], [[leikillinen]]
*Chinese: [[轻率的]], [[滑稽的]]

===Trivia===
One of only two words in English using all five vowels just once and in alphabetical order (the other being [[abstemious]]).